      "commentBody": "<span class=\"comment\"><font color=\"#000000\">Software developer, ProjectPolicy - Cambridge UK, or REMOTE<p>ProjectPolicy is a startup building Stat.io, a web application that lets people use open data to improve decision-making. Our vision is to aggregate data from hundreds of open data portals, which can then be visualised in one place. You can see a very early demo of the application over here:</p><p><a href=\"http://www.stat.io/demo/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.stat.io/demo/</a></p><p>The main technologies we're using for data processing are Python and MySQL, with a bit of Redis and MongoDB for some simple queueing and logging respectively. We're open to using any technologies if it helps get us closer to our vision.</p><p>We're looking for a software developer to join us. At the moment, the technical team consists of me (the CTO) and one intern. If you're interested or have any questions, get in touch: mike@projectpolicy.org.</p></font><p><font color=\"#000000\">You can find out more about us on our website: <a href=\"http://www.stat.io/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.stat.io/</a></font></p><p><font size=\"1\"><u><a href=\"reply?id=6311288&amp;whence=%69%74%65%6d%3f%69%64%3d%36%33%31%30%32%33%34\">reply</a></u></font></p></span>",
